'''''Subsunk''''' is a [[interactive fiction|text adventure]] game by [[Firebird Software|Firebird]] released in [[1985 in video gaming|1985]] for the [[Amstrad CPC]], [[Commodore 64]], and [[ZX Spectrum]] home computers.

== Plot ==
Ed Lines, reporter for the "Seafaring Gazette", is aboard the nuclear submarine ''Sealion'' for a routine patrol when the sub is attacked and disabled by a foreign power. The crew are taken into captivity and the sub scuttled - with the hidden journalist still aboard. He must alert headquarters with the news of what has happened and escape the doomed vessel.

== Gameplay ==
The game was produced with ''[[The Quill Adventure System|The Quill]]'' and includes simple graphics.<ref name="Sinclair User Review">{{Citation|title=Subsunk Review|newspaper=[[Sinclair User]]|date=August 1985}}</ref> The player must guide Ed Lines in his attempt to escape the stricken submarine; he must reach the [[telex]] room and issue the distress signal "SUBSUNK" to alert the authorities and bring assistance. Meanwhile, the wrecked submarine is filling with water...

It was followed by a sequel, ''[[Seabase Delta]]''.

== Reception ==
*''[[ZX Computing]]'': "... a very enjoyable game, mainly because of its sense of humour"<ref name="ZX Computing Review">{{Citation|title=Subsunk Review|newspaper=[[ZX Computing]]|date=November 1985}}</ref>
*A 1992 ''[[Your Sinclair]]'' article described it as "possibly the worst of all the games that were around at the time."<ref name="YS Adventure Chart">{{Citation|title=Adventure All-Time Greats|newspaper=[[Your Sinclair]]|date=April 1992}}</ref>

